<div class="container" id="services">
  <section class="problems">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">// failure map</div>
      <h2>The six patterns we see in every vibe-coded project</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="num">01</div>
        <h3>Architectural chaos</h3>
        <p>No separation of concerns. Business logic in UI components. API calls scattered everywhere. We restructure into layers that make sense.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="num">02</div>
        <h3>Security gaps</h3>
        <p>Raw SQL strings, hardcoded secrets, broken auth. Security often gets missed in rapid prototyping. We patch every vulnerability and add real safeguards.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="num">03</div>
        <h3>Dependency bloat</h3>
        <p>47 packages where 20 lines of code would do. Conflicting versions, abandoned libraries. We trim the dead weight and update what stays.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="num">04</div>
        <h3>Silent failures</h3>
        <p>Empty catch blocks. Functions that swallow errors. "OK" response no matter what happens. We add structured error handling and observability.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="num">05</div>
        <h3>Performance cliffs</h3>
        <p>N+1 queries, no caching, full table scans. Fine for 5 users, collapses at 500. We optimize the hot paths and add monitoring.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="num">06</div>
        <h3>Zero test coverage</h3>
        <p>No tests, no types, no CI. Moving fast meant skipping the safety nets. We add test suites, TypeScript, linting, and pipelines so you can ship with confidence.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

